{
  "doc_id": "39181",
  "text": "Alteration of the microstructure in the surface vicinity via thermochemical (e.g., laser-assisted treatments, electron beam melting, etc.) and mechanical (e.g., mechanical attrition, shot peening, etc.) pretreatment processes [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] has been successfully used for increasing the nitriding efficiency of titanium alloys. Microstructural changes thus introduced, such as significant grain refinement and nonequilibrium defects, act as diffusion shortcuts and enhance the nitriding kinetics and efficiency during the posterior plasma nitriding treatment even at low temperatures [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] .",
